Commented on #272 Unpinned tag for a non-immutable Action in workflow

The link does not work for me, is it a private repo? Otherwise, can you point me to some docs on how to make tags/releases immutable? AFAIK, git tags are mutable, and the actions docs even suggest using tags (rather than branches) for things like v2 , which I have always found weird. On your end, you can always just point to a specific git sha instead.
I hope I can avoid checking the commit every time I update, as some famous actions already support this, such as actions@checkout.
Go to the project "Setting" Check the "Enable release immutability" I think that's all.
